International Elevating Company, Libelant-Appellee, v. Steam Tug JOHN J. TIMMINS, Edward M. Timmins, Claimant-Appellant; Steam Tug AMY E. KELLER, Hudson Towboat Company, Claimant-Appellee. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 16, 1927. No. 332. Burlingham, Veeder, Masten & Eearey, of New York City (Chauncey I. Clark and C. B. Manley O’Kelley, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Harison & Hewitt, of New York City (William Harison, of New York City, of counsel)., for libelant appellee. Alexander & Ash, of New York City (Peter Alexander, of New York City, of counsel), for claimant appellee.

Before MANTON and L. HAND, Circuit Judges, and CAMPBELL, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed, with costs.
